<TITLE> Nepal PM greets Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 7 (bdnews24.com)  Nepal's prime minister Pushpa Kamal Dahal on Wednesday congratulated Sheikh Hasina for assuming the office of prime minister. The Nepalese premier hoped to see a better Bangladesh under her leadership, according to the excerpts of the message released by the foreign ministry. Chinese foreign minister Yang Jeichi congratulated new foreign minister Dipu Moni. He hoped that the friendly relations between Dhaka and Beijing would continue in future. Meanwhile, the Indian parliament speaker Somnath Chatterjee and lawyer Cherry Blair, wife of former British prime minister Tony Blair, have also congratulated Hasina, her press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told bdnews24.com. On Wednesday afternoon, Blair congratulated Hasina over phone, Azad added. bdnews
